% Handwritten A0 — Milestone 1 corpus (email_validator)
% Each requirement line maps to story ## Covers R1, R2, R3 (see stories/).

<requirements>
When the email string is valid, return True.
When the email string is invalid, return False.
Reject empty input and malformed addresses safely.
</requirements>

<vocabulary>
- valid: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
- invalid: returns an observable outcome defined by this prompt's rules
</vocabulary>

<contract_rules>
R1 - Requirement 1
When When the email string is valid, return True
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R2 - Requirement 2
When When the email string is invalid, return False
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
R3 - Requirement 3
When Reject empty input and malformed addresses safely
The module MUST satisfy this requirement with an observable outcome.
</contract_rules>

<coverage>
- R1: story__email_validation.md
- R2: story__email_validation.md
- R3: story__email_validation.md
</coverage>
